260
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:52,400
and each deme governed itself. 

261
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,840
The deme I'm looking for is one of the remotest - 

262
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:57,040
it's called Rhamnous. 

263
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:59,680
The people who lived here were mostly farmers, 

264
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:02,680
but all the male citizens voted for the council, 

265
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:05,560
and on local regulations and on by-laws. 

266
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:07,840
And right at the heart of the community, 

267
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,280
are the remains of what was once a theatre. 

268
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:15,120
This is what I've come looking for on this very hot afternoon - 

269
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:17,840
an inscription that shows us democracy 

270
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:20,000
at its most local level in operation. 

271
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:24,520
"Dionisoi" - to Dionysus... 

272
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:30,200
"Hypo tes boules" - from the Boule, 

273
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:35,160
the local council controlling this deme, here in Attica. 

274
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:38,760
And it's to Dionysus because, yes, you've guessed it, 

275
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:42,720
we're in a theatre - a theatre, the space of Dionysus. 

276
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:45,400
The privileged seats for the distinguished local clientele, 

277
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:48,640
and the stage set out before us. 

278
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:51,720
Religion, politics, theatre... 

279
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:54,240
at democracy's most local level. 

280
00:15:58,080 --> 00:16:02,600
These theatres really were far more than just places of entertainment, 

281
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:06,920
they were places where the whole deme would gather together. 

282
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:09,360
No-one's going to bother to build a theatre 

283
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:12,320
just for a couple of days of drama a year. 

284
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:13,720
But the theatres here, 

285
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:16,920
at the lowest, most basic level of the Athenian democracy, 

286
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:20,760
seem to have also been used as multi-purpose civic spaces, 

287
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:24,840
giving them all-year-round potential, not just for drama, 

288
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:28,960
but also for democracy and democratic action itself. 

289
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:33,120
And THAT is what the archaeology is really beginning to uncover - 

290
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:37,080
not only the demes, but the deme theatres, 

291
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,960
spreading across all of Attica. 

292
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:44,040
The use of theatres for democratic activity 

293
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:46,640
seems to have been the case, not just in the demes, 

294
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,880
but in the city of Athens itself. 

295
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:52,440
Every year, the democratic authorities spent a fortune 

296
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:56,080
on the Great Dionysia Festival - a drama competition 

297
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:58,440
that took place in the Theatre of Dionysus 

298
00:16:58,440 --> 00:17:00,920
in honour of the god of theatre. 

299
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:04,160
It's through understanding the different stages of this festival 

300
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:07,480
that we can get closer to understanding what ancient Athenians 

301
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:11,200
experienced when they watched and created drama. 

302
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:13,320
The festival began with a procession - 

303
00:17:13,320 --> 00:17:15,760
a rowdy affair with feasting, drinking 

304
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:18,960
and a great crowd of people parading through the streets 

305
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:23,120
with a statue of the god and a small herd of sacrificial animals. 

306
00:17:23,120 --> 00:17:27,160
When it reached the altar of the 12 Olympian Gods in the marketplace, 

307
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:29,840
the first thing that happened was a holy dance. 

308
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:35,640
The cult of Dionysus is very much 

309
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:38,680
a psychological thing. 

310
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:41,320
Wine was, of course, very important, 

311
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:43,480
everyone knows that, 

312
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:46,120
but the thing was that by drinking wine, 

313
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:48,800
you were getting closer to the god 

314
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:52,880
and the more wine you drink, the more you step out of yourself 

315
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,320
and get closer to the god. 

316
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:58,800
And that is also what happens when you're dancing, 

317
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:03,160
you're getting outside yourself, so to say, but also by, for example, 

318
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,200
wearing a mask... 

319
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:08,600
The ancient people thought that when you were wearing a mask, 

320
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:11,240
you really become someone else. 

321
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:14,320
- And the Greek word is... 
