00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:20,000
It was a religious but also a political incident, actually. 

339
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:23,960
You know, the whole city, so to say, 

340
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:26,960
steps toward the god 

341
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:30,880
in order to worship the god 

342
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:34,760
and they show not only their piety 

343
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:37,240
but also that they belong together. 

344
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:39,480
So... It's an extraordinary idea, isn't it? 

345
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:42,760
That when they take their seats in theatre, it's no longer, 

346
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:45,560
we would say in English, "It's no longer Joe Bloggs and somebody" - 

347
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:47,640
it's no longer the farmer and the individuals, 

348
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:51,280
it is a collective of people with a new identity 

349
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:55,400
- which is that of worshippers of the god Dionysus.
