00:56:34,720 --> 00:56:38,840
survive in a much harsher and more difficult world? 

1003
00:56:45,280 --> 00:56:48,840
Although the future of Athens now looked uncertain, 

1004
00:56:48,840 --> 00:56:53,160
the past century had been a spectacular era, 

1005
00:56:53,160 --> 00:56:57,320
Athens had invented and pioneered an array of things 

1006
00:56:57,320 --> 00:57:00,920
which underpin our own civilisation. 

1007
00:57:00,920 --> 00:57:03,640
From classical sculpture and architecture 

1008
00:57:03,640 --> 00:57:06,680
to new directions in philosophy and history. 

1009
00:57:08,040 --> 00:57:10,760
But for me, out of all those legacies, 

1010
00:57:10,760 --> 00:57:14,360
two stand out as the most extraordinary... 

1011
00:57:14,360 --> 00:57:16,040
First, democracy - 

1012
00:57:16,040 --> 00:57:20,040
Athens created the first democratic constitution in history 

1013
00:57:20,040 --> 00:57:22,880
which has become a beacon across the centuries. 

1014
00:57:24,440 --> 00:57:26,840
And second - at the very same time, 

1015
00:57:26,840 --> 00:57:31,080
Athens invented a powerful and incisive new art form - 

1016
00:57:31,080 --> 00:57:34,440
theatre - an innovation without which perhaps, 

1017
00:57:34,440 --> 00:57:37,240
that democracy might never have survived. 

1018
00:57:39,240 --> 00:57:44,880
Drama comes from the Greek word, "dram" - to do, to act, to perform. 

1019
00:57:44,880 --> 00:57:47,400
And if there is one thing that has become abundantly clear 

1020
00:57:47,400 --> 00:57:50,000
it's that theatre was never just mere entertainment, 

1021
00:57:50,000 --> 00:57:51,840
never a passive spectator - 

1022
00:57:51,840 --> 00:57:56,280
it was a performer in Athens' story in the ancient world. 

1023
00:57:56,280 --> 00:58:02,080
From tragedy making our most important beliefs uncomfortable, 

1024
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:04,760
to comedy questioning and policing citizenship, 

1025
00:58:04,760 --> 00:58:06,840
and keeping people in check. 

1026
00:58:06,840 --> 00:58:12,040
Theatre was an institution that plugged into religious, civic, 

1027
00:58:12,040 --> 00:58:16,200
political and military aspects of ancient Athenian society. 

1028
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:20,120
It was an extraordinary, and extraordinarily uncomfortable, 

1029
00:58:20,120 --> 00:58:24,440
risky and yet essential part of Athenian life. 

